      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAXON JEWEL (5) couldn't hold on in a strong race at Belmont last time out when bumping into a progressive type. This looks a much more suitable assignment and she rates highly on that recent form. Looks well placed here from the good draw and she can get the job done this time. OCTOBER ROX (7) flew home over 1200m at this track and should be better for that effort. He jumped favourite there and it wouldn't surprise to see him sit closer this time around. Looks open to plenty of improvement now and can play a leading role. SHOOT TO FAME (3) was well beaten when fourth last start but looks suited in a race like this today. Draws inside with the slight drop in trip and she can be in the finish. SUPERB VINTAGE (9) flew home to score here last time out and can go on with the job today. WHO SAZ YES (4) is next best.",
